In [23]:
#Attrition by Overtime and Age (01)
filtered_data = hre[['OverTime', 'Age', 'Attrition']]
grouped_data = filtered_data.groupby(['OverTime', 'Age', 'Attrition']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
width = 0.2

x = range(len(grouped_data.index))
x_labels = [f'OverTime: {o}, Age: {a}' for o, a in grouped_data.index]

plt.bar(x, grouped_data['No'], width, label='No Attrition', align='center', color='b', alpha=0.7)
plt.bar([i + width for i in x], grouped_data['Yes'], width, label='Attrition', align='center', color='r', alpha=0.7)

plt.xlabel('Combination of OverTime and Age')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.title('Attrition by OverTime and Age')
plt.xticks([i + width/2 for i in x], x_labels, rotation=45)
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

#Attrition by Overtime and Age (02)
filtered_data = hre[['OverTime', 'Age', 'Attrition']]
pivot_table = pd.crosstab(filtered_data['Age'], filtered_data['OverTime'], values=filtered_data['Attrition'], aggfunc='count')

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.title('Contour Plot of Attrition by Age and OverTime')

sns.heatmap(pivot_table, cmap='YlOrRd', annot=True, fmt='g', cbar=True, cbar_kws={'label': 'Attrition Count'})
plt.xlabel('OverTime')
plt.ylabel('Age')
plt.show()

custom_palette = ['purple', 'orange']
sns.set_palette(custom_palette)

plotnumber = 1
plt.figure(figsize=(30, 26), facecolor='white')
for col in cat_cols_2:
    if plotnumber <= 9:
        plt.subplot(4, 4, plotnumber)
        sns.countplot(x=col, hue='Attrition', data=hre)
        plt.title("Attrition distribution by " + col)
        ax = plt.gca()
        total_height = len(hre['Attrition'])
        for p in ax.patches:
            percentage = '{:.1f}%'.format(100 * p.get_height() / total_height)
            x = p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2
            y = p.get_height()
            ax.annotate(percentage, (x, y), ha='center')
        plotnumber += 1
plt.show()
